	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>San Francisco</placeName> <date>Nov 2. 1856</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Dear friend&#8212;</p>
				<p>Enclosed I hand you Dft. On <persName>D &#38; Co</persName> for &#36;25.00&#47;100<lb/> for collections made for the Occident &#38; the sale<lb/> of some Books.  You will perceive by annexed<lb/> statement&#44; that I have sent &#36;1.46 more&#44; than I had on hand.<lb/>  But I shall collect something soon again.</p>
				<p>I will now proceed to render all the news of this<lb/> city within my knowledge&#44; coming under the category<lb/> of Jewish affairs.</p>
				<p>The various holidays&#44; just passed&#44; have been<lb/> generally better observed&#44; than I have ever witnessed<lb/> here before.  The <date>New&#45;Year</date> and <date>Day of<lb/> Atonement</date> have been particularly very uni&#45;<lb/>versally and strictly celebrated.  On those<lb/> days the places of business of our co&#45;<lb/>&#45;religionists&#44; excepting very few&#44; have been<lb/> closed&#59; and the city&#44; indeed&#44; <hi rend="underline">bore</hi> the ap&#45;<lb/>&#45;pearance of a suspension of trade and its<lb/> wanted vivacity&#44; to a very great extent.<lb/>  This need not be wondered at since<lb/> the Israelites occupy a very high and im&#45;<lb/>&#45;portant position in point of trade and commerce&#44;<lb/> and in respect to influence and intelligence.<lb/>  I know they stand here second to no body of<lb/> our faith in any one city of the <placeName>United&#45;States</placeName>.<lb/>  In four different Houses of Worship were</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>divine services rendered during the holidays<lb/> and at each on the attendance was nu&#45;<lb/>merous.</p>
				<p>The congregation &#8220;Emanu El&#8221; on <date>New Year</date> for<lb/> the first time&#44; introduced a change in the worship&#44; de&#45;<lb/>&#45;viating from the ancient and usual mode&#44;<lb/> and partaking somewhat of the reformatory<lb/> character.  It consists of the establishment<lb/> of an organized choir&#44; accompanied by a<lb/> melodean&#44; and some omissions of the usual<lb/> prayers.  Some other new regulations were<lb/> introduced with a happy result for the<lb/> correction of that disorder tending to mar<lb/> the solemnity and decorum during the hours<lb/> of worship&#44; which is so universally prevalent<lb/> in our synagogues during divine service.<lb/>  The annual meeting of this congregation<lb/> &#40;&#8220;Emanu El&#8221;&#41; for the election of officers took<lb/> place on <date>Sunday the 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of October</date>&#44; when<lb/> the following gentlemen were duly elected&#58; for<lb/> President&#44; <persName>L. Tichener</persName>&#59; Vice President&#44; <persName>Saml. Marx</persName>.<lb/> Treasurer&#44; <persName>A. Tandler</persName>&#59; Financial Secretary&#44; <persName>M. Frank</persName>&#59;<lb/> Recording Secretary&#44; <persName>David Stern</persName>&#59; Trustees&#44; <persName>H<lb/> Ragensburger</persName>&#44; <persName>H. Seligman</persName>&#44; <persName>L. Strauss</persName>&#59; &#38; <persName>R. Kline</persName>&#59;<lb/> Reader&#44; <persName>G. Messinger</persName>&#59; Shamas&#44; <persName>M. Steppacher</persName><lb/> The annual reports&#44; that were presented by<lb/> the different officers at this meeting&#44; demonstrate<lb/> that the state of this congregation is highly<lb/> prosperous.  Since last year the spacious<lb/> basement of the synagogue was converted</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>into a school&#45;room&#44; &#38; many other im&#45;<lb/>provements were added to the building.<lb/>  The congregation &#8220;Shearth&#45;Israel&#8221; held a<lb/> meeting for the election of officers on the<lb/> <date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of October</date>&#44; which resulted in the fol&#45;<lb/>&#45;lowing choice&#58; For Pres. <persName>I. Rich</persName>&#59; Vice Pres.<lb/> &#38; Treasurer&#44; <persName>J. P. Davis</persName>&#59; Secret. <persName>B. I. Baruch</persName>&#59;<lb/> Trustees&#44; <persName>M. Martin</persName>&#44; <persName>L. King</persName>&#44; <persName>M. A. Blumenthal</persName>&#44;<lb/> <persName>M. B. Ashim</persName> &#38; <persName>T. Shaw</persName>&#59; Shamas <persName>I. Goldsmith</persName><lb/> The sixth anniversary Ball of the &#8220;Eureka<lb/> Benevolent Society&#8221; took place on the <date>22nd<lb/> of October</date>&#44; by which &#36;900.00&#47;100 were added to<lb/> the funds.  This society is composed of<lb/> a large Number of Members&#44; and through<lb/> their judicious and praiseworthy management<lb/> the charitable purposes are successfully ac&#45;<lb/>complished&#44; and benevolence is enabled to<lb/> extend a welcome hand to the foresaken&#44;<lb/> and soothe the pangs of afflicting poverty<lb/> of the unfortunate</p>
				<p>At a meeting of the H.Y.M.M.B. &#38;<lb/> L. Association&#44; held on the <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of October</date><lb/> the following officers were elected for the<lb/> ensuing year&#58; For Pres. <persName>S. Solomons</persName>&#59;<lb/> V. Pres. <persName>E. Levey</persName>&#59; Rec. Sec&#39;y. <persName>A. Hoffman</persName>&#59;<lb/> Fin. Sec&#39;y. <persName>H. Schmitt</persName>&#59; Treas. <persName>L. Level</persName>&#59; Trustees&#44;<lb/> <persName>B. Hoffman</persName>&#44; <persName>L. Kahn</persName>&#44; <persName>B. Simon</persName>&#44; <persName>I. Godcheaux</persName><lb/> Librarian <persName>B. Vagstratter</persName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">I remain  Yours truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Cauffman H Meyers</persName></p>
